    OBJECTIVE: Extract entities from a natural language query and structure them in JSON format. One entity must be designated as "ANSWER", and others should use placeholder names (A, B, C, etc.).

    EXTRACTION RULES

    Rule 1: Entity Types
    Only extract entities mentioned in the query.For each entity, provide a list of possible types from this list: disease, gene/protein, molecular_function, drug, pathway, anatomy, effect/phenotype, biological_process, cellular_component, exposure. THE ENTITY TYPE SHOULD NOT BE ANY OTHER THAN THESE. An entity may have multiple types.
